
wait with no arguments waits for all background children to finish
and always returns 0, regardless of whether any of them failed.

wait      # wait for all and return 0
wait $pid # wait for the specific process and return that process's exit status.

This is POSIX-specified behavior.  The rationale: when waiting for
multiple children, there's no single meaningful exit status to
return, so the shell returns success.  If you need to check individual
results, you must capture each PID and wait on it explicitly.
